    "In contrast, full network training, especially with the Base-Cyclic design, provides enhanced accuracy and faster inference times.",
    "This dual-strategy approach facilitates comprehensive automatic analysis of Foraminifera, including benthic species from the last interglacial period in a sediment core from the north-eastern Pacific and planktonic species, suggesting a significant advancement in the automated classification and analysis of micropaleontological data.",
    "Karaderi et al. (2022) explore the application of deep metric learning for classifying planktonic foram shells from microscopic images.",
